node.text:
Based on a true story.

I feel like this trend was made for me😂 I get this phrase all the time from the older folks in my life. I love ‘em but dang, why is the main goal in life to find your future husband?

I posted this video on TikTok first and got a lot of comments so I wanted to clear up my message behind this video. I am by no means a solo, female traveller. I like to travel and hike with friends and family🌞 My idea with this was to show that I choose to spend my time outside, doing what I love, exploring new places… rather than going on dates and spending hours on dating apps to find a man. While there’s absolutely nothing wrong with that—I’ve done that on and off—I just rather hope that someone will come into my life in a different way😚 I’m excited to share my life with someone, but until then, I’ll be in the mountains doing my thing✌🏼

The tune is by @boy.with.uke and it’s called “two moons” 🎶

node.text:
Fall photos incoming!🍂 I know it’s not technically fall just yet but I can’t wait any longer. 

Cooler temperatures, no bugs, fall colours, less people outside—so many good things about this (short but sweet) season. 

Photo shot by @chrisrlocke

node.text:
The seasons are changing and I couldn’t be more excited😌🤍🍂

Who else thinks September is the best month of the year?!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ANGELA LIGUORI in Beautiful British Columbia with @explorecanada, @angelaliggs, @juliiathompson, @womenwhoexplore, @allaboutadventures, @womenwhohike, @hikingtheglobe, and @hikingbangers. May be an image of 1 person, nature and mountain.

node.text:
Mother Nature put on a little show for my friends and I on this particular morning that included mountain layers, light rays and fluffy clouds. It wasn’t the full cloud inversion we hoped for.. but it sure was stunning to watch😌☁️ 

Photo shot by @juliiathompson

node.text:
Ah hot springs… pure bliss😌🤍

(I’m super tired from getting up at 4:30am and hiking 20km+ this morning so that’s the best caption I could come up with🙈)

node.text:
No better way to wake up🌲This cute a-frame is 100 square feet with a retractable awning you can open for more space (and to hear the river & birds a little bit better)😌

Check out @river.therapy.retreat to stay in the cabin and @rivertherapyfishingco to book adventure tours♥️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ANGELA LIGUORI in Beautiful British Columbia with @angelaliggs, @juliiathompson, and @allaboutadventures. May be an image of nature, sky and mountain.

node.text:
This hike was so steep (2,000m of gain with an overnight backpack) that on the way down I questioned why I do willingly do these things😂 

The knee pain and sore muscles went away after a day or two and all I have left is good memories. Always worth it!

Photo shot by @juliiathompson

node.text:
My genuine reaction caught on camera😌 

This is one of the best feelings…. and I hope that each and every person can feel this one day. 

(Backstory: I was taking a video explaining how tired I was and I looked up to see these peaks that I never even knew you could see from this summit😌🏔)
